Item caption and stat code: SVNA1 - Visit NRQ - Sub-study visit performed at this time point instead.
SVNA2 - Visit NRQ - Patient consented to the sub-study but is not participating due to Investigator discretion.
SVNA1 - Visit NRQ - Sub-study visit performed at this time point instead.
Action Taken in response to the AE (multiple items can be selected if 'None' is blank)
AEONGO - Is the adverse event ongoing?
AEREL_DEV - Relationship of the AE to the device
AEREL_PRO - Relationship of the AE to the device procedures
AESER - Is the Adverse Event serious?
AESEV - What is the severity of the Adverse Event?
DSPERF2_IC - Did the patient consent to the Sub-Study?
DSPRV1_IC - Protocol Version at Time of Main Study Consent
DSSTDAT1_IC - Date Patient Signed Main Study Consent

DVDESC - Detailed Deviation Narrative (include details relating to the source of the deviation,
its impact on the study, and the immediate action taken)
EGASSESS - Overall assessment of the ECG
EGOTHFIND - Were there any other notable ECG findings?
IEYN - Was the patient eligible for the study?
DMCBP - Is the patient of child-bearing potential?
SVUPDES - Reason for Unscheduled Visit / Assessment
Check all assessments that were performed as part of this unscheduled visit
DMCBP_CONT - Contraception method(s) used by this patient
Ensure a pregnancy test is performed before the procedure
DSTERMAE_COMP - Adverse Event Number and Term that caused Withdrawal
Assessments relating to the main study should NOT be performed on this patient
IEREASND - Reason eligibility review not performed
VSREASND_HTWT - Reason height and weight not measured

SVTEST_OTH_DESC - Description of 'Other' assessments not possible to be captured on above forms (include the date and time of the assessment / sample collection and the outcome / result, if applicable)
AESCONG - Was the adverse event associated with a congenital anomaly or birth defect?
AESDISAB - Did the adverse event result in disability or permanent damage?
AESDTH - Did the adverse event result in death?
AESHOSP - Did the adverse event result in initial or prolonged hospitalization for the subject?
AESLIFE - Was the adverse event life-threatening?
AESMIE - Was the adverse event a medically important event not covered by other serious criteria?
AESNOTYN - Has Sponsor been notified of the SAE?
DMNCBP_REAS - Reason for non-child-bearing potential (e.g. postmenopausal, surgically sterile etc.)
DSTERMPD_COMP - Protocol Deviation Number that caused Withdrawal
EGFINDLIST - List other notable ECG findings
DSTERMOTH_COMP - Specify Other Reason(s) for Withdrawal
DSPRV2_IC - Protocol Version at Time of Sub-Study Consent
DSSTDAT2_IC - Date Patient Signed Sub-Study Consent
EGCLSIG - Were the abnormality(s) clinically significant?
Assessments relating to the sub-study should NOT be performed on this patient
AEHENDAT_YN - Has the patient been discharged from hospital yet?
DSTERMSF_COMP - Reason for Screen Failure (include eligibility criteria numbers failed)
AEACNOTH_PROC - Procedural Intervention (procedure or surgery performed)
AEACNOTH_TESTS - Assessment / Test (e.g. ECG, lab test)
